"{\"uid\": \"article127\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"code and would replace the drive for personal profit with the drive towards participation in and service for the greater benefit of humanity and the Earth.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 155, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Imagine this movement would gradually dissolve the old nation-states, power blocs and cultural borders.\", \"from\": 156, \"to\": 259, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Communities would be home to people from all over the world, including refugees from crisis areas.\", \"from\": 260, \"to\": 358, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Once people have again found home in a real community, they no longer need to violently defend the construct of their \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"fatherland\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" against people from elsewhere.\", \"from\": 359, \"to\": 526, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"(Is not nationalism anyways just a compensation for the sense of \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"home\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" we have lost as humanity!)\", \"from\": 527, \"to\": 631, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In order to start such a transformative movement, we need models which show that a new society based on communitarian coexistence, trust between people and regenerative autonomy is possible.\", \"from\": 633, \"to\": 823, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We need places for new types of holistic research to develop the ecological, technological, economic, political, social, spiritual and sexual structures necessary for our society to become once again compatible with life, nature and humanity's deeper longings and motivations.\", \"from\": 824, \"to\": 1100, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"There already exists an enormous amount of knowledge and solutions in this direction, but they need to be fused into a coherent blueprint, a concept for a new global culture.\", \"from\": 1101, \"to\": 1275, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Healing Biotopes Plan attempts to introduce such a process of cultural creation.\", \"from\": 1276, \"to\": 1360, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"You say this is too utopian and far-fetched?\", \"from\": 1362, \"to\": 1406, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Well, the more we see the dimensions of the current global crisis we also see the necessity for a fundamental redesign of the way we inhabit this planet.\", \"from\": 1407, \"to\": 1560, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This is not the time to be \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"realistic\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" in the narrow conventional sense, because if we think like this we do not even have to begin.\", \"from\": 1561, \"to\": 1699, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It is not the time to think about slow incremental change, but to think about complete revolution, to dare a lot, dream big and see the most beautiful vision of what our world can be.\", \"from\": 1700, \"to\": 1883, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This is what it is to be radical in times of such tremendous transformation.\", \"from\": 1884, \"to\": 1960, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Evolution does not advance gradually, but in leaps - once a pattern of organization is no longer functional, living systems undergo a period of turbulence until they suddenly leap into a more complex pattern of organization.\", \"from\": 1962, \"to\": 2186, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This is the process we are undergoing as a species right now, the process we are participating in and co-creating.\", \"from\": 2187, \"to\": 2301, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The clearer our vision, the more we can help birth the future we want.\", \"from\": 2302, \"to\": 2372, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We cannot leave this up to some president, institution or guru; nobody else will do it for us.\", \"from\": 2373, \"to\": 2467, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Now is the moment to start building a new humane culture and it begins by seeing its actual possibility.\", \"from\": 2468, \"to\": 2572, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I have written more about this in the Fall 2016 print edition of Tikkun Magazine.\", \"from\": 2574, \"to\": 2655, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I hope you will subscribe to Tikkun so you read it there atwww.tikkun.org/subscribe.\", \"from\": 2656, \"to\": 2740, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Martin Winiecki, born in Dresden, Germany in 1990, is a writer, speaker, and coordinator of the Institute for Global Peace Work at Tamera, Portugal.\", \"from\": 2742, \"to\": 2890, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"*************************************************************************************************************************************************  The Meaning of Brexit  JEFFREY SACHS  PROJECT SYNDICATE  JUNE 25, 2016  NEW YORK - The Brexit vote was a triple protest: against surging immigration, City of London bankers, and European Union institutions, in that order.\", \"from\": 2892, \"to\": 3260, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It will have major consequences.\", \"from\": 3261, \"to\": 3293, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Donald Trump's campaign for the US presidency will receive a huge boost, as will other anti-immigrant populist politicians.\", \"from\": 3294, \"to\": 3417, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Moreover, leaving the EU will wound the British economy, and could well push Scotland to leave the United Kingdom - to say nothing of Brexit's ramifications for the future of European integration.\", \"from\": 3418, \"to\": 3614, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Brexit\", \"from\": 3616, \"to\": 3622, \"entities\": []}]}"